# RFC — Design Before Code

Major features require an **Accepted RFC** in `docs/18-rfc/` before production code.

## When RFC Is Required

- New API resource group, bounded context module, AI feature, n8n workflow family
- Cross-cutting API + UI + worker deliverable
- Case-scoped feature with matter wall impact

## When to Stop and Draft RFC

If user asks to implement a major feature and no Accepted RFC exists:

1. Read `docs/18-rfc/README.md` index
2. Use `.ai/tasks/create-rfc.md` + `docs/18-rfc/_template.md`
3. Do **not** write `services/` or `apps/` code until RFC is Accepted (unless user explicitly overrides)

## RFC vs ADR

| RFC | ADR |
|-----|-----|
| What to build | Binding architecture choice |
| `docs/18-rfc/` | `docs/13-decisions/` |

## PR Requirement

Link `RFC-NNN` in PR body; verify behavior matches accepted design.

## Platform Readiness (before auth / business logic)

Do not implement JWT, RBAC, domain logic, or matter walls until [`platform-readiness-gate.md`](../../docs/14-playbooks/platform-readiness-gate.md) passes (`make verify-platform`).

Full process: `.ai/handbook/rfc-process.md`
